## Goal

Implement the discovery loop where a node polls `immutable://pending/` for new entries, reads each envelope, replays validation, and writes either an attestation (`immutable://attestation/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey} -> true`) or rejection (`immutable://rejection/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey} -> "reason"`). This is the node-side behavior for Stage 1 (Attestation) of the confirmation protocol.

## Background

Per CONFIRMATION.md section 4 (Node Behavior), each node in the network:

1. Polls `immutable://pending/` via `list()` to discover new submissions
2. For each entry, extracts the envelope hash from the value
3. Checks if it already attested: `read("immutable://attestation/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey}")`
4. If not attested, reads the envelope and runs full validation replay
5. Writes attestation (if valid) or rejection (if invalid)

This loop is structurally similar to `connect()` in `b3nd-listener` -- it's a polling transport that processes messages. The key difference is that instead of decrypting/calling a handler/encrypting, it replays validation and writes a verdict.

The discovery loop should use cursor-based tracking (from G2-A1-02) to avoid reprocessing old pending entries.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `createDiscoveryLoop()` function exported from `libs/firecat-protocol/confirmation.ts`
- [ ] Polls `immutable://pending/` at a configurable interval
- [ ] Skips entries where `immutable://attestation/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey}` already exists
- [ ] Skips entries where `immutable://rejection/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey}` already exists
- [ ] Calls `replayValidation()` on discovered envelopes
- [ ] Writes `immutable://attestation/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey} -> true` on validation success
- [ ] Writes `immutable://rejection/{envelopeHash}/{selfKey} -> "reason"` on validation failure
- [ ] Returns a `start()` / `stop()` interface like `connect()`
- [ ] Tracks cursor to avoid reprocessing old entries
- [ ] Tests verify the full discover-validate-attest cycle
- [ ] Tests verify that already-attested entries are skipped

## Implementation Guide

1. Define the discovery loop configuration:
   ```typescript
   export interface DiscoveryLoopConfig {
     client: NodeProtocolInterface;
     nodePublicKeyHex: string;
     pollIntervalMs?: number;
     onAttestation?: (envelopeHash: string) => void;
     onRejection?: (envelopeHash: string, reason: string) => void;
     onError?: (error: Error, uri: string) => void;
   }

   export interface DiscoveryLoop {
     poll(): Promise<number>;
     start(): () => void;
   }
   ```

2. Implement the polling logic:
   ```typescript
   export function createDiscoveryLoop(config: DiscoveryLoopConfig): DiscoveryLoop {
     const { client, nodePublicKeyHex, pollIntervalMs = 5000 } = config;
     const processed = new Set<string>();

     async function poll(): Promise<number> {
       const pendingList = await client.list("immutable://pending");
       if (!pendingList.success) return 0;

       let count = 0;
       for (const item of pendingList.data) {
         if (processed.has(item.uri)) continue;

         // Read the pending record to get envelope hash
         const pending = await client.read<string>(item.uri);
         if (!pending.success || !pending.record) continue;

         const envelopeHashUri = pending.record.data;
         // Extract just the hash part
         const envelopeHash = envelopeHashUri.replace("hash://sha256/", "");

         // Check if already attested/rejected
         const attested = await client.read(`immutable://attestation/${envelopeHash}/${nodePublicKeyHex}`);
         if (attested.success) { processed.add(item.uri); continue; }
         const rejected = await client.read(`immutable://rejection/${envelopeHash}/${nodePublicKeyHex}`);
         if (rejected.success) { processed.add(item.uri); continue; }

         // Replay validation
         const verdict = await replayValidation(client, envelopeHashUri);

         if (verdict.verdict === "valid") {
           await client.receive([
             `immutable://attestation/${envelopeHash}/${nodePublicKeyHex}`,
             true,
           ]);
           config.onAttestation?.(envelopeHash);
         } else {
           await client.receive([
             `immutable://rejection/${envelopeHash}/${nodePublicKeyHex}`,
             verdict.reason,
           ]);
           config.onRejection?.(envelopeHash, verdict.reason);
         }

         processed.add(item.uri);
         count++;
       }
       return count;
     }

     // start/stop similar to connect()
   }
   ```

3. Implement `replayValidation()` as described in CONFIRMATION.md section 4:
